value.value: 環椎後頭関節脱臼
separation of the joints formed by the occipital condyles and the atlas (C-1)
肘窩形態異常

any structural anomaly of the deep triangular depression on the posterior side of the humerus, superior to the trochlea, in which the summit of the olecranon is received during extension of the forearm
肘頭形態異常

any structural anomaly of the large bony prominence at the proximal end of the ulna which articulates with the olecranon fossa of the humerus and is palpable at the posterior aspect of the elbow; while the olecranon is an attachment site for several muscle groups including the flexor carpi ulnaris and anconeus, the major muscle attachment is that of the triceps brachii muscle
肘頭欠如
missing the large bony prominence at the proximal end of the ulna which articulates with the olecranon fossa of the humerus and is palpable at the posterior aspect of the elbow
肘頭矮小化
size reduction of the large bony prominence at the proximal end of the ulna which articulates with the olecranon fossa of the humerus and is palpable at the posterior aspect of the elbow
腓腹筋種子骨の欠如
missing the small sesamoid bones situated behind the condyles of the femur
膝蓋骨脱臼

complete displacement of the patella (kneecap) from its normal position in the patellofemoral groove (trochlea), the V-shaped notch on the front of the femur; the most common direction for a dislocated patella is lateral
三角骨形態異常
any structural anomaly of the bone in the proximal row of the carpus that has a pyramidal shape and that is situated between the lunate and pisiform bones
三角骨欠如
missing the bone in the proximal row of the carpus that has a pyramidal shape and that is situated between the lunate and pisiform bones
関節可動性低下
reduced ability to move joints in a full range of motion and with ease
手首脱臼
displacement of any of the small carpal bones which make up the wrist out of their normal position in the wrist joint
滑膜関節腔形態異常

any structural anomaly of the minute space enclosed by the synovial membrane and articular cartilages in a synovial joint; it is the site at which the articulating surfaces of the bones contact each other; it contains synovial fluid, a highly viscous, hyaluronic acid–rich fluid that lubricates the joint surfaces
滑膜関節膜形態異常

any structural anomaly of the connective tissue membrane that lines the cavity of a synovial joint and produces the synovial fluid; it lines all internal surfaces of the cavity except for the articular cartilage of the bones
甲状軟骨の縮小
size reduction of the largest of the laryngeal cartilages
甲状軟骨欠損
missing the largest of the laryngeal cartilages
甲状軟骨形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the thyroid cartilage, typically resulting in decreased size

label.value: abnormal superior horn of thyroid cartilage morphology

value.value: 甲状軟骨の上角形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal superior horn of thyroid cartilage morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of either of a pair of upward projections from the posterior border of the thyroid cartilage; it is long and narrow, directed upward, backward, and medialward, and ends in a conical extremity, which gives attachment to the lateral hyothyroid ligament

label.value: abnormal inferior horn of thyroid cartilage morphology

value.value: 甲状軟骨の下角形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal inferior horn of thyroid cartilage morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of either of a pair of downward projections from the posterior border of the thyroid cartilage; it is short and thick, directed downward, with a slight inclination forward and medialward, and presents, on the medial side of its tip, a small oval articular facet for articulation with the side of the cricoid cartilage
輪状軟骨の縮小
size reduction of the most inferior of the laryngeal cartilages
輪状軟骨欠如
missing the most inferior of the laryngeal cartilages
輪状軟骨形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the cricoid cartilage, typically resulting in decreased size
軟骨関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of any joint that lacks a joint cavity and involves bones that are joined together by either hyaline cartilage or fibrocartilage; there are two main types: synchondroses (or primary cartilaginous joints) where the bones are united by hyaline cartilage, and symphyses (or secondary cartilaginous joints) where the bones are united by a layer of fibrocartilage
肋軟骨関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the hyaline cartilaginous joint (synchondrosis) between each rib and its costal cartilage; the articulation is between the cup-shaped depression in the sternal end of a rib and the lateral end of a costal cartilage; the rib and its cartilage are firmly bound together by the continuity of the periosteum of the rib with the perichondrium of the cartilage; no movement normally occurs at these joints
癒合形態異常
any structural anomaly of any cartilaginous joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by fibrocartilage; a symphysis is a slightly movable joint (amphiarthrosis)
線維性連結形態異常

any structural anomaly of any joint that lacks a joint cavity and involves bones that are joined together by dense fibrous connective tissue, consisting mainly of collagen; most (but not all) fibrous joints are immovable (synarthroses)
靭帯結合形態異常

any structural anomaly of any fibrous joint where the gap between two adjacent bones may be narrow, with the bones joined by ligaments, or the gap may be wide and filled in by a broad sheet of connective tissue called an interosseous membrane; syndemoses are slightly moveable (amphiarthrodial)
膝蓋下脂肪体形態異常

any structural anomaly of the partly adipose wedge-shaped mass formed in the anterior region of the knee that is intracapsular but extrasynovial (and thus extra-articular); it extends superiorly from the patella and alar folds to the tibia and infrapatellar bursa and is delimited anteriorly by the patellar ligament and joint capsule and posteriorly by the synovial membrane
膝の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the segment of the hindlimb that corresponds to the joint connecting a hindlimb stylopod and zeugopod
橈骨小頭形態異常

any structural anomaly of the proximal articular surface of the radius that forms part of the elbow joint and that is palpable on the lateral side of the elbow, immediately distal to the lateral epicondyle of the humerus; the radial head articulates with the ulna at the proximal radioulnar joint and with the humerus at the radiohumeral joint; at the proximal radioulnar joint, the radial head sits in the radial notch of the proximal ulna and is held in place by the annular ligaments; at the radiohumeral joint, the radial head sits adjacent to the capitellum of the humerus
橈骨小頭脱臼
a dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint
ラキティック ロザリオ
abnormal expansion of the anterior rib ends at the costochondral junctions; most frequently seen in rickets as nodularity (prominent bony knobs) at the costochondral junctions
橈骨サイズ拡大
greater than average size of the short bone of the lateral forearm
橈骨サイズ縮小
less than average size of the short bone of the lateral forearm
胸鎖関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the synovial joint between the clavicle and the manubrium of the sternum; it is the only attachment of the upper limb to the axial skeleton and consists of the sternal end of the clavicle, the manubrium of the sternum, and part of the first costal cartilage; the articular surfaces are covered with fibrocartilage (as opposed to hyaline cartilage); the joint is separated into two compartments by a fibrocartilaginous articular disk
披裂軟骨欠損
missing the paired triangular cartilages that normally are located postlaterally at the level of the thyroid cartilage
披裂軟骨矮小化
size reduction of the paired triangular cartilages located postlaterally at the level of the thyroid cartilage
披裂軟骨低形成
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the arytenoid cartilage, typically resulting in decreased size
小喉頭蓋

size reduction of the most superior of the laryngeal cartilages, which is found at the root of the tongue and folds back over the entrance to the larynx during swallowing, preventing inhalation of food or drink
喉頭蓋形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the epiglottis, typically resulting in decreased size
喉頭蓋肥大

increased size of the most superior of the laryngeal cartilages, which is found at the root of the tongue and folds back over the entrance to the larynx during swallowing, preventing inhalation of food or drink
喉頭蓋過形成
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the epiglottis, typically resulting in increased size
脛大腿関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the modified hinge synovial joint that joins the distal femur to the proximal tibia; it is the weight-bearing joint of the knee; the articulation occurs between the medial and lateral femoral condyles and the tibial condyles
膝蓋大腿関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of the synovial joint between the condyles of the femur and the articular surface of the patella
腕尺関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of the simple hinge-type synovial joint between the trochlea on the medial aspect of the distal end of the humerus and the trochlear notch on the proximal ulna
第一胸肋関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the synchondrosis type of cartilaginous joint in which hyaline cartilage unites the first rib to the manubrium of the sternum.; it forms an immobile joint (synarthrosis); the rest of the sternocostal joints are synovial plane joints
喉頭裂
presence of a gap in the posterior laryngotracheal wall with a continuity between the larynx and the esopahagus
尺骨サイズ縮小
less than average size of the medial and larger of the two bones of the forearm
尺骨サイズ増大
greater than average size of the medial and larger of the two bones of the forearm
尺骨茎状突起形態異常

any structural anomaly of the cylindrical, pointed, palpable projection from the medial and posterior aspect of the head of the ulna, to the tip of which is attached the ulnar collateral ligament of the wrist
尺骨茎状突起矮小化
reduced size of the cylindric, pointed, palpable projection from the medial and posterior aspect of the head of the ulna, to the tip of which is attached the ulnar collateral ligament of the wrist
